1 STATE OF OKLAHOMA
2 1st Session of the 60th Legislature (2025)
3 FLOOR SUBSTITUTE
FOR ENGROSSED
4 SENATE BILL NO. 970 By: Weaver of the Senate
5 and
6 West (Kevin) of the House
7
8
9 FLOOR SUBSTITUTE
10 An Act relating to child custody; requiring notice to
custodial parent by noncustodial parent; providing
11 that the parent is not required to disclose certain
information; providing exception; providing that the
12 parent be held in indirect contempt of court in
certain circumstances; providing for codification;
13 and providing an effective date.
14
15
16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
17 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
18 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 4-107b of Title 43A, unless
19 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
20 A custodial parent shall receive notice from the noncustodial
21 parent, or the noncustodial parent’s representative, if the
22 noncustodial parent is unable to comply with court-ordered
23 visitation or any other court-ordered requirement for any reason.
24 Unless ordered otherwise by the court, the noncustodial parent shall
Req. No. 13661 Page 1
1 not be required to disclose the reason the parent is unable to
2 comply. A noncustodial parent who violates the provisions of this
3 section shall be in indirect contempt of court.
4 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
